olive oil
2 potato
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
20 g butter
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 apple
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
2 clove garlic
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning

• Bring a medium saucepan of lightly salted water to the boil.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Finely chop garlic. Zest lemon to get a
pinch, then slice into wedges. Roughly chop baby spinach leaves.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help zest the lemon.

• Cook potato in the boiling water until easily pierced with a fork,
12-15 minutes. Drain and set aside.
• Return saucepan to medium-high heat with the butter. Cook 1/2 the garlic,
stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add a generous squeeze of lemon juice, the lemon zest, chicken-style
stock powder and a dash of water and bring to the boil. Remove from heat,
then return potato to the pan and toss to coat.
• Stir through grated Parmesan cheese, then lightly crush potato with a fork.
Cover to keep warm.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help crush the potatoes!

• While the potato is cooking, combine Nan's special seasoning, the
remaining garlic and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl. Add chicken
breast strips, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, cook chicken strips in batches, until browned and cooked
through, 3-4 minutes each side.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple.
• In a large bowl, combine slaw mix, apple, baby spinach and 1/2 the
mayonnaise. Season to taste.
• Divide cheesy crushed lemon potatoes, apple slaw and Nan's chicken strips
between plates.
• Spoon any resting juices over the chicken. Serve with any remaining lemon
wedges and mayo. Enjoy!